OL,3,CBristol City Council refuses to join
OL,4,Crevolt over asylum seeker hotels
OL,6,FBut perhaps unsurprisingly - given the
OL,7,Foverwhelming presence of counter-
OL,8,Fprotesters at these demonstrations -
OL,9,FBristol City Council's leader Tony
OL,10,FDyer has joined the likes of Brighton
OL,11,Fand Hove in saying he isn't
OL,12,Fconsidering legal action against the
OL,13,Fuse of hotels.
OL,15,FHe says: "Bristol is a long-
OL,16,Festablished place of sanctuary. We are
OL,17,Fa diverse city and are proud to
OL,18,Fwelcome and provide safety for people
OL,19,Fseeking sanctuary from a wide range of
OL,20,Fbackgrounds."
