OL,3,CBristol City Council refuses to join
OL,4,Crevolt over asylum seeker hotels
OL,6,FAccording to latest Home Office data,
OL,7,F802 asylum seekers were staying in
OL,8,Fhotels in Bristol at the end of June -
OL,9,Fthe sixth highest number in the
OL,10,Fcountry. That number has fallen since
OL,11,F2023, but has gone up slightly since
OL,12,FMarch this year.
OL,14,FIn a statement given to ITV, Mr Dyer
OL,15,Fsaid: "As a city of Sanctuary, we will
OL,16,Fcontinue to support and show
OL,17,Fcompassion to people when they need it
OL,18,Fmost."
