OL,6,FHe admitted hotel accommodation "is
OL,7,Fnot always the best way to meet the
OL,8,Fhealth and wellbeing needs of people
OL,9,Fseeking sanctuary and to help them
OL,10,Fintegrate with existing communities"
OL,11,Fbut maintained that the local
OL,12,Fauthority is committed to fostering an
OL,13,Fenvironment that supports asylum
OL,14,Fseekers.
OL,16,FNational figures show the number in UK
OL,17,Fhotels has risen by 8% under Labour,
OL,18,Fdespite the party's promise to end
OL,19,Ftheir use by the end of this
OL,20,FParliament.
